<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,1090,219,1268]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,223,1148,1172]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[273,365,1147,1171]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species is preserved in the Musée royal de l’Afrique centrale in Tervuren. I did not see the 
<typeStatus box="[393,490,1179,1203]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">holotype</typeStatus>
. The redescription was done from a specimen (‘Cotype’) from the Bernhauer collection (FMNH). However, Bernhauer never described the species, therefore this specimen (‘comparatype’) does not have any type status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
